<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="161" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="161">
The Latin adjective 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">truncatus</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">a</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">um</emphasis>
refers to the truncate shape of the superior appendages posterior margin in lateral view.
</paragraph>
